The /api/v1/discuss/stream endpoint is registered in the router with AI concurrency middleware and requires authentication via JWT or API token. When a POST request arrives, the server sets SSE headers (Content-Type: text/event-stream, Cache-Control: no-cache, Connection: keep-alive), sends an initial 'connected' event, then subscribes to the event bus with a wildcard listener. As events arrive on the subscribed channel, the handler marshals each event to JSON and writes it as an SSE message (event: <type>
data: <json>

), flushing immediately so tokens stream to the client in real-time. A 30-second heartbeat ticker keeps the connection alive, and the loop exits when the request context is canceled.
